43c35b0e-8915-4ba6-8265-9845dba9e269.0650bb12-c04a-4318-9e33-737e5bf21c7e.prompt=Password\: 43c35b0e-8915-4ba6-8265-9845dba9e269.07e96843-e014-47b3-87c8-6fa32fc66ebe.prompt=Password\: 43c35b0e-8915-4ba6-8265-9845dba9e269.0fb5ad7d-26ac-4935-a199-e5150d2e786e.prompt=Close session?\: 43c35b0e-8915-4ba6-8265-9845dba9e269.2b3463e8-eaee-445d-8515-822d764e1b68.prompt=VMWare Host\: 43c35b0e-8915-4ba6-8265-9845dba9e269.2d5503ae-f807-4c85-b715-a9a88c8efe9b.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults". As a result, the context key whose name is in the keyName input will be appended with the string from the input resultText.

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Returns\:
The the value of the context variable it appended to.

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

43c35b0e-8915-4ba6-8265-9845dba9e269.385d49fa-f86e-40c4-b85b-089116dd64b3.prompt=VMWare Host\: 43c35b0e-8915-4ba6-8265-9845dba9e269.47d7ebc2-53a5-4c56-ae48-d8778add8622.description=
Search for VMWare objects of type propsType and their properties (propsPathset) from a root object (if any) specified by propsRootObjType and propsRootObj. Retrieve each object's properties one at a time from an initial search query as the one used for the SQL Query operation. Please see VMWare Integration Guide for more details.

Inputs\:
host - VMWare host hostname or IP.
user - VMWare username.
password - VMWare user's password.
port - Port to connect on.
protocol - Connection protocol (http or https).
closeSession - Close the internally kept VMWare Infrastructure API session at completion of operation (true, false).
propsType - VMWare properties type (Task, Datacenter, VirtualMachine, Network etc.) to filter on. Type of object results desired.
propsPathset - Property filter's pathset, comma-delimited (eg. name, info.name, runtime.host).
propsRootObjType - The type of the Managed Object Reference (such as VirtualMachine, HostSystem, ComputeResource, ResourcePool, Alarm, Datacenter, Datastore) to begin the search on. Leaving this blank will default the root object to the root folder of the ESX or VC host. 
propsRootObj - The value of the reference (such as vm-123, datastore-123, network-123) used as a root object. Leaving this blank will default the root object to be the root folder of the ESX or VC host. 

Responses\:
success - The operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong. See returnResult for details.
no more - There are no more results to retrieve.

Returns\:
numberOfResults - Number of results from the query remaining to be retrieved.
returnResult - Query result item or reason for failure.

43c35b0e-8915-4ba6-8265-9845dba9e269.92bf988a-9cf1-465f-9474-0d03a0739b0b.transition.description=Found VM\: ${itemVMID} \: ${itemName} 43c35b0e-8915-4ba6-8265-9845dba9e269.9e749e0e-64c2-4006-a0a2-6f2050fe84fb.transition.description=Found ${count} VMs in cluster. 43c35b0e-8915-4ba6-8265-9845dba9e269.bd442a82-ef99-4428-a846-50ad25d6d623.prompt=VMWare User\: 43c35b0e-8915-4ba6-8265-9845dba9e269.c0d08766-b875-451a-9f8d-015d2a455684.prompt=VMWare User\: 43c35b0e-8915-4ba6-8265-9845dba9e269.ce18cc0e-a37d-4638-b4be-330b32759838.description=
Search for VMWare objects containing a given name (ignoring case). Retrieve each object one at a time from an initial search query as the one used for the SQL Query operation.

Inputs\:
host - VMWare host hostname or IP.
user - VMWare username.
password - VMWare user's password.
port - Port to connect on.
protocol - Connection protocol (http or https).
closeSession - Close the internally kept VMWare Infrastructure API session at completion of operation (true, false).
propsType - VMWare properties type (VirtualMachine, Network, ComputeResource, ResourcePool, HostSystem, Datastore, Datacenter) to filter on. Type of object results desired.
nameToMatch - The string to perform a case insensitive contains match to.  Only objects that contain this string in their name will be matched.  If not specified, all objects of the specified type will be matched.

Responses\:
success - The operation completed successfully and there are more results available.
failure - Something went wrong.
no more - There are no more results to retrieve.

Returns\:
numberOfResults - Number of results from the query remaining to be retrieved.
returnResult - Query result item or operation result.
43c35b0e-8915-4ba6-8265-9845dba9e269.description=
Returns a list of virtual machines (VMs) in a cluster.

Inputs\:
    host - VMware vCenter hostname or IP.
    user - VMware username.
    password - VMware user's password.
    port - Port to connect on.
Examples\: 443, 80
    protocol - Connection protocol.
Valid values\: "http",  "https"
    clusterName - Name of cluster to list virtual machines from.
    delimiter - A delimiter for separating values in the vmid and name result lists.
Example\: |

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed successfully.
    failure - Something went wrong.

Returns\:
    count - Number of virtual machines found in the cluster.
    vmid - List of virtual machine ids found in the cluster delimited by delimiter.
    name - List of virtual machine names found in the cluster delimited by delimiter.
